  "body": "Hi,\r\nMy node some times got errors in log like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nJun  4 14:13:36 ethereum geth[11105]: WARN [06-04|14:13:36] Synchronisation failed, retrying         err=\"block body download canceled (requested)\"\r\nJun  4 14:13:41 ethereum geth[11105]: WARN [06-04|14:13:41] Synchronisation failed, retrying         err=\"block download canceled (requested)\"\r\nJun  4 14:14:23 ethereum geth[11105]: WARN [06-04|14:14:23] Synchronisation failed, dropping peer    peer=7d430cf25060b77d err=timeout\r\n\r\nJun  4 14:22:25 ethereum geth[11105]: WARN [06-04|14:22:25] Header broke chain ordering              number=5731216 hash=f97bb1â€¦e995a8 expected=5731217\r\nJun  4 14:22:25 ethereum geth[11105]: WARN [06-04|14:22:25] Synchronisation failed, dropping peer    peer=8ef752b0d5875c5b err=\"action from bad peer ignored\"\r\nJun  4 14:23:34 ethereum geth[11105]: WARN [06-04|14:23:34] Synchronisation failed, dropping peer    peer=51f0168b3af7a788 err=\"no peers available or all tried for download\"\r\n\r\nJun  4 14:32:58 ethereum geth[11105]: WARN [06-04|14:32:58] Head headers broke chain ordering        peer=d6ce9f8623da477f index=0 requested=5731068 received=5731262\r\nJun  4 14:32:58 ethereum geth[11105]: WARN [06-04|14:32:58] Synchronisation failed, dropping peer    peer=d6ce9f8623da477f err=\"retrieved hash chain is invalid\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd some times sync far from mainnet, sometimes 0 to 0 with mainnet.\r\nAnd of course after error in log - i see unsync near 2-5 blocks.\r\n\r\nAll this error it is normal?\r\nOr i Can something to do to eliminate this error?\r\nCan i reduce error?\r\n\r\nP.S. Why error - it is chain from bad node? Can i use fail2ban? ))",
